# BitTrust Frontend Rules

## 1. Project Info
- **Project:** BitTrust (Decentralized reputation protocol on Stacks for AI agents and wallets)
- **Concept:** Calculates on-chain trust scores monetized via x402 (HTTP 402 micro-payments).
- **Vibe:** Institutional monitoring tool, credit bureau for bots. Serious, dark, matte (no glassmorphism).

## 2. Code Quality & Standards
- Write clean, strictly typed TypeScript code. Avoid `any` types.
- Avoid deeply nested components. Extract complex logic into custom hooks.
- Use meaningful, self-documenting variable and function names.

## 3. File Structure
- **No monolithic files.** Break UI down into isolated, reusable components.
- Shared utilities go in `src/lib/`.
- Hooks go in `src/hooks/`.
- UI primitives go in `src/components/ui/`.
- Next.js App Router rules apply (`app/page.tsx`, `app/layout.tsx`).

## 4. UI Components (shadcn/ui)
- Use **shadcn/ui** for UI primitives (buttons, cards, inputs, dialogs).
- Combine shadcn components with standard Tailwind utility classes for layout.
- Build UI by combining customizable, accessible components rather than writing custom CSS.

## 5. Design Guidelines (Tailwind)
- **Colors:**
  - Background: `#020617` (main app)
  - Cards: `#020817` / `#050816`
  - Primary Accent: `#F7931A` (Bitcoin amber) — Hover `#C56F11`
  - Secondary Accent: `#5546FF` (Purple)
  - Semantic: `#10B981` (Success), `#FACC15` (Warning), `#EF4444` (Danger)
  - Text: `#E5E7EB` (Main), `#9CA3AF` (Muted)
- **Typography:** Inter or Satoshi, 14-15px base.
- **Component Classes:**
  - Cards: `rounded-xl bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-800 shadow-sm`
  - Primary Button: `bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-slate-950 font-medium rounded-lg`
  - Secondary Button: `bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 text-slate-100`
  - Badges: `rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs uppercase`
  - Inputs: `bg-slate-900 border border-slate-700 focus:border-amber-500`

## 6. Micro-UX & Interactivity
- Single primary action per view (e.g., "Connect wallet" on Home).
- Skeletons for loading states (no spinners).
- Fast hover/focus transitions (150-200ms ease-out).
- Empty States: Short and actionable (e.g., "No reputation yet. Start using DeFi protocols...").
- Copy: Concrete, no hype. Make risk immediately obvious with colors and labels.